   "source": [
    "# AAIT (III–II) – EXP-12 (Improved)\n",
    "## Developing a Simple Chatbot using Python — Enhanced Version\n",
    "\n",
    "**Improvements added over the base version:**\n",
    "1. ✅ New intents — Attendance, Lab Timings, Experiment List\n",
    "2. ✅ Fuzzy Matching — using `difflib.SequenceMatcher` for typo tolerance\n",
    "3. ✅ Conversation Memory — context-aware follow-up handling\n",
    "4. ✅ FAQ from CSV — load extra Q&A pairs from a `.csv` file at runtime\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tools:** Python (VS Code / Google Colab)  \n",
    "**Mapped CO:** CO5\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 0 — Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import random\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import csv\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "from difflib import SequenceMatcher"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Bot config + Extended Intent Knowledge Base\n",
    "\n",
    "**New intents added:**\n",
    "- `attendance` — questions about attendance rules\n",
    "- `lab_timings` — questions about lab schedule/hours\n",
    "- `experiment_list` — asking which experiments are in AAIT"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "BOT_NAME = \"AAIT Helpdesk Bot\"\n",
    "EXIT_COMMANDS = {\"exit\", \"quit\", \"bye\", \"stop\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "INTENTS = {\n",
    "    \"greeting\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"hi\", \"hello\", \"hey\", \"good morning\", \"good afternoon\", \"good evening\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"Hello! I am the AAIT Helpdesk Bot. How can I help you?\",\n",
    "            \"Hi! Ask me about AAIT tools, lab experiments, or submissions.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"aait_course\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"what is aait\", \"aait\", \"application of ai tools\", \"ai tools course\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"AAIT stands for Application of AI Tools. In this lab you learn tools like Trello, Visual Paradigm, Figma, Teachable Machine, Colab, and Tableau.\",\n",
    "            \"AAIT is a hands-on lab course where you plan, design, and build small AI prototypes using modern tools.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"tools_info\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"trello\", \"figma\", \"visual paradigm\", \"vp\", \"teachable machine\", \"colab\", \"tableau\", \"github\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"AAIT tools include: Trello (project planning), Visual Paradigm (flowcharts/UML), Figma (UI wireframes), Teachable Machine/Colab (ML models), and Tableau (visualization).\",\n",
    "            \"Let me know the specific tool (Trello/Figma/VP/Colab/Teachable Machine) and I can tell you its AAIT use case.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"lab_info\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"lab\", \"experiment\", \"practical\", \"record\", \"procedure\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"In AAIT lab: understand the task, follow the procedure, generate your own output, and write a reflection in your own words.\",\n",
    "            \"For lab work: always keep your outputs ready and be prepared to explain your steps and results.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"submission\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"submit\", \"submission\", \"google form\", \"deadline\", \"pdf\", \"link\", \"upload\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"Submission is usually through Google Form / link upload. Ensure your file/link is accessible and outputs are clearly visible.\",\n",
    "            \"Before submitting: re-run your notebook/script fully and verify all outputs are generated by you.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"evaluation\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"marks\", \"evaluation\", \"viva\", \"grading\", \"exam\", \"comprehensive\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"AAIT evaluation checks: correct workflow, outputs, explanation, and reflection. Be ready for viva questions on your own work.\",\n",
    "            \"For exams/viva: know your algorithm steps, flowchart meaning, and why your tool/model choice fits the problem.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"time_now\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"time now\", \"current time\", \"what time\", \"time please\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\"DYNAMIC_TIME\"]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"thanks\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"thank you\", \"thanks\", \"thx\", \"thank u\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"You're welcome!\",\n",
    "            \"Glad to help. Ask me anytime.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    \"goodbye\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"bye\", \"goodbye\", \"see you\", \"see ya\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"Goodbye! All the best for your AAIT lab!\",\n",
    "            \"See you. Keep practicing and keep your outputs ready.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ── NEW INTENT 1: Attendance ──────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "    \"attendance\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"attendance\", \"absent\", \"leave\", \"bunked\", \"missed lab\", \"percentage\", \"minimum attendance\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"Minimum attendance required is usually 75%. Missing lab sessions can affect your eligibility for the end-semester exam.\",\n",
    "            \"If you missed a lab, check with your faculty for a make-up session or alternate submission option. Attendance rules vary by section.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ── NEW INTENT 2: Lab Timings ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "    \"lab_timings\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"lab timing\", \"lab time\", \"lab hours\", \"when is lab\", \"lab schedule\", \"what time lab\", \"lab session\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"AAIT lab timings depend on your section timetable. Please check the official notice board or your faculty's announcement.\",\n",
    "            \"Lab sessions are typically 2–3 hours. Refer to your class timetable or ask your section's faculty for the exact slot.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ── NEW INTENT 3: Experiment List ─────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "    \"experiment_list\": {\n",
    "        \"patterns\": [\"experiment list\", \"list of experiments\", \"how many experiments\", \"all experiments\", \"syllabus\", \"exp list\", \"which experiments\"],\n",
    "        \"responses\": [\n",
    "            \"AAIT lab typically covers 12+ experiments including: Trello project planning, Figma UI design, Visual Paradigm flowcharts, Teachable Machine models, Google Colab ML notebooks, Tableau dashboards, and more.\",\n",
    "            \"The experiment list covers planning (Trello), design (Figma/VP), modelling (Teachable Machine/Colab), and visualization (Tableau). Check your lab manual for the full list.\"\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "UNKNOWN_RESPONSES = [\n",
    "    \"Sorry, I didn't understand that. Try asking about AAIT, tools, lab, attendance, submission, or evaluation.\",\n",
    "    \"I'm not sure about that. Ask me about AAIT tools, lab timings, or submissions.\"\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 — Preprocess user input"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def preprocess(text: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Lowercase, remove punctuation, and normalize spaces.\"\"\"\n",
    "    text = text.lower().strip()\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9\\s]\", \" \", text)\n",
    "    text = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n",
    "    return text"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 — Improvement 2: Fuzzy Matching with difflib\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why?** Users often mistype — \"attendence\", \"submision\", \"trelllo\".  \n",
    "We use `SequenceMatcher` to compute similarity ratio (0.0 to 1.0).  \n",
    "If ratio ≥ threshold (0.75), we treat it as a match.\n",
    "\n",
    "The updated `match_intent` tries exact/keyword match first, then falls back to fuzzy."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "FUZZY_THRESHOLD = 0.75  # similarity ratio needed for a fuzzy match\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def fuzzy_score(a: str, b: str) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return similarity ratio between two strings (0.0 – 1.0).\"\"\"\n",
    "    return SequenceMatcher(None, a, b).ratio()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def match_intent(user_text: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return best-matching intent using keyword scoring + fuzzy fallback.\"\"\"\n",
    "    text = preprocess(user_text)\n",
    "    tokens = set(text.split())\n",
    "\n",
    "    best_intent = None\n",
    "    best_score = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ── Pass 1: Exact keyword / phrase scoring ────────────────────────────\n",
    "    for intent, data in INTENTS.items():\n",
    "        score = 0\n",
    "        for pat in data[\"patterns\"]:\n",
    "            pat_clean = preprocess(pat)\n",
    "            if \" \" in pat_clean:          # phrase → substring match\n",
    "                if pat_clean in text:\n",
    "                    score += 2\n",
    "            else:                          # single word → token match\n",
    "                if pat_clean in tokens:\n",
    "                    score += 1\n",
    "        if score > best_score:\n",
    "            best_score = score\n",
    "            best_intent = intent\n",
    "\n",
    "    if best_score > 0:\n",
    "        return best_intent\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ── Pass 2: Fuzzy fallback ────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "    best_fuzzy_intent = None\n",
    "    best_fuzzy_score = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "    for intent, data in INTENTS.items():\n",
    "        for pat in data[\"patterns\"]:\n",
    "            pat_clean = preprocess(pat)\n",
    "            # Compare full text against pattern, and each token against pattern\n",
    "            scores_to_check = [fuzzy_score(text, pat_clean)] + [\n",
    "                fuzzy_score(tok, pat_clean) for tok in tokens\n",
    "            ]\n",
    "            top = max(scores_to_check)\n",
    "            if top > best_fuzzy_score:\n",
    "                best_fuzzy_score = top\n",
    "                best_fuzzy_intent = intent\n",
    "\n",
    "    if best_fuzzy_score >= FUZZY_THRESHOLD:\n",
    "        return best_fuzzy_intent\n",
    "\n",
    "    return \"unknown\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 — Improvement 3: Conversation Memory\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why?** A user might ask \"Tell me about Trello\" then follow up with \"what about VP?\"  \n",
    "Without memory, the bot treats the second message in isolation.  \n",
    "\n",
    "**How it works:**\n",
    "- `context` dict tracks `last_intent` and `last_tool`.\n",
    "- If the new message is very short (≤ 3 words) and matches tool-follow-up keywords, we inject context.\n",
    "- Example follow-ups handled: \"and VP?\", \"what about figma\", \"tell me more\"."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Tool-specific responses for follow-up memory\n",
    "TOOL_DETAILS = {\n",
    "    \"trello\":            \"Trello is used in AAIT for project planning — creating boards, lists, and cards to track experiment tasks.\",\n",
    "    \"figma\":             \"Figma is used to create UI wireframes and prototypes — you design the interface of your AI application.\",\n",
    "    \"visual paradigm\":   \"Visual Paradigm (VP) is used for flowcharts, UML diagrams, and DFDs to document your system design.\",\n",
    "    \"vp\":                \"VP (Visual Paradigm) helps you draw flowcharts and use-case diagrams for your AAIT experiments.\",\n",
    "    \"teachable machine\": \"Teachable Machine lets you train image/sound/pose classifiers in-browser — no code needed!\",\n",
    "    \"colab\":             \"Google Colab is a free Python notebook environment used to write and run ML code in AAIT.\",\n",
    "    \"tableau\":           \"Tableau is used to create interactive dashboards and data visualizations for your dataset.\",\n",
    "    \"github\":            \"GitHub is used to version-control and share your code/notebooks as part of AAIT submissions.\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "FOLLOW_UP_TRIGGERS = {\"what about\", \"tell me more\", \"and\", \"also\", \"explain\", \"more about\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def resolve_follow_up(user_text: str, context: dict) -> str | None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    If the message looks like a follow-up (short + follow-up trigger),\n",
    "    check if it names a tool we know about and return a specific response.\n",
    "    Returns None if not a follow-up situation.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    text = preprocess(user_text)\n",
    "    word_count = len(text.split())\n",
    "\n",
    "    is_follow_up = any(trigger in text for trigger in FOLLOW_UP_TRIGGERS)\n",
    "    is_short = word_count <= 5\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not (is_follow_up or (is_short and context.get(\"last_intent\") == \"tools_info\")):\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Check if any known tool is mentioned\n",
    "    for tool, detail in TOOL_DETAILS.items():\n",
    "        if tool in text:\n",
    "            context[\"last_tool\"] = tool\n",
    "            return detail\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Generic \"tell me more\" about last tool\n",
    "    if \"tell me more\" in text and context.get(\"last_tool\"):\n",
    "        tool = context[\"last_tool\"]\n",
    "        return TOOL_DETAILS.get(tool, None)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return None"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5 — Improvement 4: Load FAQ from CSV\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why?** Separating data from code makes it easy to add new Q&A without editing Python.  \n",
    "A teacher/admin can edit the CSV; the bot picks it up automatically.\n",
    "\n",
    "**CSV format (faq.csv):**\n",
    "```\n",
    "keyword,response\n",
    "plagiarism,Plagiarism in lab outputs will result in zero marks. Always generate your own results.\n",
    "github desktop,GitHub Desktop is a GUI client to commit and push code without using the command line.\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "FAQ_DB: dict[str, str] = {}   # populated by load_faq()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def create_sample_faq_csv(path: str = \"faq.csv\"):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create a sample faq.csv if it doesn't exist (for demo purposes).\"\"\"\n",
    "    if os.path.exists(path):\n",
    "        return\n",
    "    rows = [\n",
    "        [\"keyword\", \"response\"],\n",
    "        [\"plagiarism\", \"Plagiarism in lab outputs leads to zero marks. Always generate your own results.\"],\n",
    "        [\"github desktop\", \"GitHub Desktop is a GUI tool to commit and push code without using the terminal.\"],\n",
    "        [\"kaggle\", \"Kaggle is a platform for datasets and ML competitions. Useful for finding datasets for AAIT projects.\"],\n",
    "        [\"make up\", \"For missed labs, contact your faculty about make-up sessions. Policies vary by section.\"],\n",
    "        [\"marks split\", \"AAIT marks are typically split between lab performance, record, and viva/comprehensive.\"],\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    with open(path, \"w\", newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
    "        csv.writer(f).writerows(rows)\n",
    "    print(f\"[INFO] Created sample '{path}'. Edit it to add more FAQs.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_faq(path: str = \"faq.csv\"):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Load keyword→response pairs from CSV into FAQ_DB.\"\"\"\n",
    "    global FAQ_DB\n",
    "    create_sample_faq_csv(path)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        with open(path, newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
    "            reader = csv.DictReader(f)\n",
    "            for row in reader:\n",
    "                key = preprocess(row[\"keyword\"])\n",
    "                FAQ_DB[key] = row[\"response\"]\n",
    "        print(f\"[INFO] Loaded {len(FAQ_DB)} FAQ entries from '{path}'.\")\n",
    "    except FileNotFoundError:\n",
    "        print(f\"[WARN] '{path}' not found. No FAQ entries loaded.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def check_faq(user_text: str) -> str | None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Check if user text matches any FAQ keyword. Returns response or None.\"\"\"\n",
    "    text = preprocess(user_text)\n",
    "    for keyword, response in FAQ_DB.items():\n",
    "        if keyword in text:\n",
    "            return response\n",
    "        # fuzzy fallback for FAQ too\n",
    "        if fuzzy_score(text, keyword) >= FUZZY_THRESHOLD:\n",
    "            return response\n",
    "    return None\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load FAQ at import time\n",
    "load_faq()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6 — Generate response (with all improvements integrated)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_response(user_text: str, context: dict) -> str:\n",
    "    # 1. Check dynamic time intent first\n",
    "    if match_intent(user_text) == \"time_now\":\n",
    "        context[\"last_intent\"] = \"time_now\"\n",
    "        return f\"Current time is {datetime.now().strftime('%I:%M %p')}.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    # 2. Improvement 3 — Check conversation memory / follow-up\n",
    "    follow_up_reply = resolve_follow_up(user_text, context)\n",
    "    if follow_up_reply:\n",
    "        context[\"last_intent\"] = \"tools_info\"\n",
    "        return follow_up_reply\n",
    "\n",
    "    # 3. Improvement 4 — Check CSV FAQ database\n",
    "    faq_reply = check_faq(user_text)\n",
    "    if faq_reply:\n",
    "        context[\"last_intent\"] = \"faq\"\n",
    "        return faq_reply\n",
    "\n",
    "    # 4. Improvement 2 — Intent matching (with fuzzy fallback inside match_intent)\n",
    "    intent = match_intent(user_text)\n",
    "    context[\"last_intent\"] = intent\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Track last tool mentioned for memory\n",
    "    text = preprocess(user_text)\n",
    "    for tool in TOOL_DETAILS:\n",
    "        if tool in text:\n",
    "            context[\"last_tool\"] = tool\n",
    "            break\n",
    "\n",
    "    if intent == \"unknown\":\n",
    "        return random.choice(UNKNOWN_RESPONSES)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return random.choice(INTENTS[intent][\"responses\"])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7 — Chat loop"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def chat():\n",
    "    print(f\"{BOT_NAME}: Hi! Type 'exit' to quit.\")\n",
    "    context = {\"last_intent\": None, \"last_tool\": None}\n",
    "\n",
    "    while True:\n",
    "        user_input = input(\"You: \").strip()\n",
    "        if not user_input:\n",
    "            print(f\"{BOT_NAME}: Please type something (or type 'exit' to quit).\")\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        cleaned = preprocess(user_input)\n",
    "        if cleaned in EXIT_COMMANDS:\n",
    "            print(f\"{BOT_NAME}: Goodbye! All the best for your AAIT lab.\")\n",
    "            break\n",
    "\n",
    "        reply = get_response(user_input, context)\n",
    "        print(f\"{BOT_NAME}: {reply}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 8 — Demo (non-interactive)\n",
    "\n",
    "Shows all 4 improvements in action."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def demo():\n",
    "    tests = [\n",
    "        # Original intents\n",
    "        (\"Hi\",                        \"greeting\"),\n",
    "        (\"What is AAIT?\",             \"aait_course\"),\n",
    "        # New intents\n",
    "        (\"What is the attendance rule?\", \"attendance (NEW)\"),\n",
    "        (\"When is the lab session?\",   \"lab_timings (NEW)\"),\n",
    "        (\"Show me the experiment list\", \"experiment_list (NEW)\"),\n",
    "        # Fuzzy match test (typos)\n",
    "        (\"submision deadline?\",        \"fuzzy → submission\"),\n",
    "        (\"attendence percentage\",      \"fuzzy → attendance\"),\n",
    "        # Memory / follow-up\n",
    "        (\"Tell me about Trello\",       \"tools_info\"),\n",
    "        (\"What about Figma?\",          \"memory follow-up → figma detail\"),\n",
    "        (\"and VP?\",                    \"memory follow-up → vp detail\"),\n",
    "        # CSV FAQ\n",
    "        (\"What about plagiarism?\",     \"FAQ from CSV\"),\n",
    "        (\"Tell me about Kaggle\",       \"FAQ from CSV\"),\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    context = {\"last_intent\": None, \"last_tool\": None}\n",
    "    print(\"=\" * 65)\n",
    "    print(\" AAIT Helpdesk Bot — Improvement Demo\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\" * 65)\n",
    "    for msg, label in tests:\n",
    "        reply = get_response(msg, context)\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n[{label}]\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  You : {msg}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Bot : {reply}\")\n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 65)\n",
    "\n",
    "demo()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 9 — Run the interactive chatbot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "chat()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary of Improvements\n",
    "\n",
    "| # | Improvement | How it works |\n",
    "|---|-------------|--------------|\n",
    "| 1 | **New Intents** | Added `attendance`, `lab_timings`, `experiment_list` with realistic patterns |\n",
    "| 2 | **Fuzzy Matching** | `difflib.SequenceMatcher` catches typos like "attendence", "submision" (threshold 0.75) |\n",
    "| 3 | **Conversation Memory** | `context` dict tracks `last_intent` and `last_tool`; follow-ups like "what about VP?" return tool-specific answers |\n",
